properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 2:37AM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTER WEATHER WILL IMPACT TRAVEL THIS WEEKEND...

.Another round of snow will arrive late this afternoon and early
evening, bringing snowfall totals of 2 to 6 inches, heaviest
along the lakeshore. Along with the snowfall, considerable blowing
and drifting snow will occur, especially from the Fox Valley to
the lakeshore counties. The worst conditions will occur along the
lakeshore areas, where the highest snowfall totals are expected,
and northeast winds will gust to 35 to 40 mph. Travel conditions
will be significantly impacted.

The strong northeast winds will also result in increased
potential for lakeshore flooding, shoreline erosion, and ice
shoves on the bay and Lake Winnebago.

* WHAT...For the first Winter Weather Advisory, snow and blowing
snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to one inch. Winds
gusting as high as 35 mph. For the second Winter Weather
Advisory, snow and blowing snow expected. Total snow
accumulations of 1 to 3 inches. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Calumet County.

* WHEN...For the first Winter Weather Advisory, until 6 AM CST
early this morning. For the second Winter Weather Advisory,
from 3 PM this afternoon to 6 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. Gusty winds could
bring down tree branches, resulting in localized power outages.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
